Package Main.Others

This package holds the other java classes which cannot be clearly fitted into another package. These include GameFrame which loads in the entire game, GraphicsMain which calls GameFrame, HomeMenu which is the home menu for the game, InfoScreen which describes the game mechanics in detail and LevelGeneration which generates the bricks for all 5 levels for the GameBoard.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    GameFrame
    Public class GameFrame is responsible for loading between all the different screens in the game.
    GameSounds
    Public class GameSounds is responsible for adding audio to the game such as BGM and sound effects.
    GraphicsMain
    Public class GraphicsMain is used to load the GameFrame which will load all the different screens of the game and then show the HomeMenu.
    HomeMenu
    Public class HomeMenu is the first screen the player sees when starting the game.
    InfoScreen
    Public class InfoScreen is used to display information about the game and explains all the different functionalities of the game so that the player may better enjoy the game.
    LevelGeneration
    Public class LevelGeneration is responsible for generating the brick for all 5 levels of the game.
